# OpenRouter API Keys Configuration Example
# ================================================

# Step 1: Get free API keys from https://openrouter.ai
# Step 2: Copy your API key and paste below
# Step 3: Done! Users can start using the app without any configuration

# Primary API Key (Required)
# This key will be used by default for all requests
VITE_OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-your-api-key-here

# Additional API Keys (Optional)
# You can provide multiple keys for:
# - Load balancing between different API keys
# - Using different free tier keys for different models
# - Fallback if one key hits rate limits
# Format: comma-separated list (no spaces)
VITE_OPENROUTER_API_KEYS=sk-or-v1-key-1,sk-or-v1-key-2,sk-or-v1-key-3

# OpenRouter API Configuration
VITE_OPENROUTER_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1

# App Configuration
VITE_REPO_NAME=SAKHA-2
VITE_APP_NAME=SAKHA AI

# ================================================
# HOW TO GET FREE OPENROUTER API KEYS:
# ================================================
# 1. Go to https://openrouter.ai
# 2. Click "Sign In" or "Sign Up"
# 3. Complete registration
# 4. Go to Dashboard → API Key
# 5. Copy your API key (looks like: sk-or-v1-...)
# 6. Paste it in VITE_OPENROUTER_API_KEY above
# 7. Rebuild with: npm run build:prod
# 8. Done! Users can now use all models without configuration!
#
# FREE MODELS AVAILABLE:
# - Llama 3 70B (Meta)
# - Mistral Large
# - Google Gemini
# - DeepSeek
# - Cohere Command
# And 10+ more!
